-- Southern Cross’ Banks Agree to Suspend Covenant, Times Reports
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   B r o w n i n g
-- 2010-11-28T10:33:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-28/southern-cross-banks-agree-to-suspend-covenant-times-reports.html
Southern Cross Healthcare Ltd.’s 
banks have agreed to suspend a covenant on loans to the U.K.
nursing home company, the  Sunday Times  reported, without saying
where it got the information.  Barclays Plc and Lloyds Banking Group Plc have agreed to
waive the covenant, the newspaper said. Southern Cross declined
to comment, according to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan Browning in London 
 jbrowning9@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vidya Root at 
 vroot@bloomberg.net . 